{"name": "sentry-telegram-py3", "metadata": {"name": "sentry-telegram-py3", "version": "0.6.2", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Topic :: Software Development :: Bug Tracking", "Topic :: Software Development :: Quality Assurance", "Topic :: System :: Monitoring"], "home_page": "https://github.com/vortland/sentry-telegram", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Plugin for Sentry which allows sending notification via Telegram messenger.", "upload_time": 1735153472}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  codecov: |-\n    ```{image} https://codecov.io/gh/vortland/sentry-telegram/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n    :alt: Coverage Status\n    :target: https://codecov.io/gh/vortland/sentry-telegram?branch=master\n    ```\n  pypi: |-\n    ```{image} https://badge.fury.io/py/sentry-telegram-py3.svg\n    :target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/sentry-telegram-py3\n    ```\n  travis: |-\n    ```{image} https://app.travis-ci.com/vortland/sentry-telegram.svg?branch=master\n    :alt: Build Status\n    :target: https://app.travis-ci.com/vortland/sentry-telegram\n    ```\n---\n\n# Sentry Telegram {{ travis }} {{ codecov }} {{ pypi }}\n\nPlugin for Sentry which allows sending notification via [Telegram](https://telegram.org/) messenger.\n\nPresented plugin tested with Sentry 22.12.0.\n\n> **DISCLAIMER**: Sentry API is under development and [is not frozen](https://docs.sentry.io/server/plugins/).\n\n## How will it look like\n\n```{image} https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vortland/sentry-telegram/master/docs/images/telegram-window.png\n:alt: How will it look like\n:target: https://github.com/vortland/sentry-telegram/blob/master/docs/images/telegram-window.png\n```\n\n## Installation\n\n1. Install this package\n\n```bash\npip install sentry-telegram-py3\n```\n\n2. Restart your Sentry instance.\n\n3. Go to your Sentry web interface. Open `Settings` page of one of your projects.\n\n4. On `Integrations` (or `Legacy Integrations`) page, find `Telegram Notifications Python3` plugin and enable it.\n\n5. Configure plugin on `Configure plugin` page.\n\n   See [Telegram's documentation](https://core.telegram.org/bots#3-how-do-i-create-a-bot) to know how to create `BotAPI Token`.\n\n6. Done!\n"], "modules": [{"name": "sentry_telegram_py3", "documentation": ["Plugin for Sentry which allows sending notification via Telegram messenger.", "coding: utf-8"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin", "documentation": ["coding: utf-8"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin.TelegramNotificationsOptionsForm", "bases": ["notify.NotificationConfigurationForm"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin.TelegramNotificationsOptionsForm.api_origin", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin.TelegramNotificationsOptionsForm.api_token", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin.TelegramNotificationsOptionsForm.receivers", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin.TelegramNotificationsOptionsForm.message_template", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin.TelegramNotificationsPlugin", "bases": ["CorePluginMixin", "notify.NotificationPlugin"], "methods": [{"name": "sentry_telegram_py3.plugin.TelegramNotificationsPlugin.is_configured", "asynchro